President Obama has nominated Judge Abdul K. Kallon to serve on the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit. Judge Kallon is currently a United States District Judge in the Northern District of Alabama. He has a strong background in litigation and counseling, having worked on corporate civil defense matters at both the district and appellate court levels. Judge Kallon was born in Sierra Leone and immigrated to the United States in 1980. He earned his A.B. from Dartmouth College in 1990 and his J.D. from the University of Pennsylvania Law School in 1993. Before joining the bench, he served as a law clerk and worked at the law firm of Bradley Arant Boult Cummings, eventually becoming a partner. Throughout his career, Judge Kallon has been actively involved in the Birmingham community, serving on various boards and participating in state and federal bar associations. President Obama commended his record of service and fair decision-making, stating that he will be a valuable addition to the Eleventh Circuit.